					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "The Inscriber"
			x: 26.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}

		{
			dependencies: ["AE01000000000003"]
			description: ["Assembled processors are the logic cores of the ME network. Logic Processors (gold foil + printed circuit) handle routing. Calculation Processors (Certus foil + printed circuit) handle storage indexing and autocrafting job resolution. Engineering Processors (diamond foil + printed circuit) handle high-throughput operations and are consumed in the most demanding network components. Produce at least 16 of each before beginning ME Controller assembly — the controller alone consumes several, and each Drive, Terminal, and Autocrafting CPU component adds to the count."]
			id: "AE01000000000004"
			rewards: [{
